revision.text:
{{COI|date=February 2018}} {{advert|date=January 2017}}
The '''AMC Institute''' (AMCI) is the global membership organization of the [[association management company]], or AMC, industry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2016/03/22/822214/10161241/en/PSAV-Announces-Partnership-with-AMCI.html|title=PSAV Announces Partnership with AMCI|last=Services|first=PSAV Presentation|website=GlobeNewswire News Room|language=en-US|access-date=2016-05-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|title=How to Start a Home-Based Event Planning Business|last=Moran|first=Jill S.|publisher=Taylor Trade Publishing|year=2015|isbn=978-1493011704|location=|pages=202}}</ref> Headquartered in Alexandria, Virginia, U.S., AMCI counts as members more than 180 AMC member organizations employing 3,500 people and representing 2.8 million individual members throughout the U.S., Canada, Europe and Asia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/?page=amcinfographic|title=AMCs: A Growing Global Industry - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-05-31}}</ref>
As of 2016, AMCI represents both the world's largest association management company, [[SmithBucklin]], as well as the world's largest professional conference organiser, [[MCI Group]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/members/?id=16926818|title=SmithBucklin - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-05-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/members/?id=16928186|title=MCI Group - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-05-31}}</ref>
The total budget for associations managed by AMCI members is more than $1.5 billion.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/?page=history|title=History - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-05-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://globenewswire.com/news-release/2016/03/22/822214/10161241/en/PSAV-Announces-Partnership-with-AMCI.html|title=PSAV Announces Partnership with AMCI|last=Services|first=PSAV Presentation|website=GlobeNewswire News Room|language=en-US|access-date=2016-05-30}}</ref>
AMCI's accreditation program is based upon the [[American National Standards Institute]]-approved standard for good AMC practices. In May 2007, to provide clearer direction to associations interested in being managed by AMCs, the institute and the [[American Society of Association Executives]] (ASAE) agreed to support a single AMC accreditation program run by the institute.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/?page=history|title=History - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-05-31}}</ref>
==History== AMCI was founded in 1963 as the Multiple Association Management Institute. It since has undergone several name changes, including the Institute of Association Management Companies (IAMC) in 1976 and the International Association of Association Management Companies (IAAMC) in 1996. In the early 2000s, AMCs from ASAE and IAAMC joined to form the AMC Institute, a marketing arm to support the promotion of the AMC model. AMCs could purchase a partnership with the AMC Institute, regardless of their membership in IAAMC or ASAE. In 2005, IAAMC changed its name to AMC Institute, assumed the AMC marketing responsibilities and, in 2006, the organization as a whole assumed the AMC Institute name to more clearly brand the AMC concept.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.amcinstitute.org/?page=history|title=History - AMC Institute (AMCI)|website=www.amcinstitute.org|access-date=2016-06-01}}</ref>
