'''Adam Franklin''' is an Australian author, entrepreneur and social media [[keynote]] speaker.<ref>http://www.bluewiremedia.com.au/speakers</ref><ref>http://www.brw.com.au/p/sections/focus/start_spreading_the_newsletter_K5EeYn061Ddm2zUNEscv8H</ref><ref>http://www.icmi.com.au/adam-franklin</ref>

Franklin published ''Web Marketing That Works: Confessions from the Marketing Trenches'' (Wiley 2014) ({{ISBN|978-0-7303-0927-7}})<ref>https://www.amazon.com/Web-Marketing-That-Works-Confessions/dp/0730309274/</ref> as a paperback and Kindle ebook with co-author [[Toby Jenkins]]<ref>http://au.wiley.com/WileyCDA/WileyTitle/productCd-0730309274.html</ref> and it became an Amazon #1 bestseller in Australia.<ref>http://www.bluewiremedia.com.au/blog/2015/06/amazon-1-bestseller-web-marketing-that-works</ref>

He co-founded his company<ref>http://www.bluewiremedia.com.au/why-choose-bluewire-media/the-bluewire-story</ref> Bluewire Media with [[Toby Jenkins]] in 2005. Franklin featured on ''Smart Company'''s "Australia's Hot 30 Under 30" list of entrepreneurs in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smartcompany.com.au/leadership/profiles/815-hot-30-under-30/hot-30-under-30-2009/9111-toby-jenkins-and-adam-franklin.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-12-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151130234211/http://www.smartcompany.com.au/leadership/profiles/815-hot-30-under-30/hot-30-under-30-2009/9111-toby-jenkins-and-adam-franklin.html |archivedate=30 November 2015 }}</ref>  In 2010 he collaborated with [[David Meerman Scott]] on the Web Strategy Planning Template which they co-branded.<ref>http://www.webinknow.com/2010/07/free-marketing-strategy-planning-template.html</ref>  This marketing strategy template was also included in the third, fourth and fifth editions of [[David Meerman Scott]]'s bestselling book The New Rules of Marketing and PR which has over 350,000 copies in print in more than 25 languages.

He co-hosts the podcast ''Web Marketing That Works''<ref>https://itunes.apple.com/au/podcast/web-marketing-that-works/id867351184</ref> and was interviewed  on the Entrepreneur On Fire podcast.<ref>http://www.eofire.com/podcast/adam-franklin-interview-of-bluewire-media-with-john-lee-dumas-of-entrepreneur-on-fire/</ref>

In 2015, Franklin's Bluewire Media blog was named the #1 Business Blog in Australia according to Smart Company<ref>http://www.smartcompany.com.au/technology/45714-australia-s-20-best-business-blogs-2015.html</ref> and was a Business Finalist for the Best Australian Blogs in 2014 according to the Australian Writers' Centre.<ref>http://www.writerscentre.com.au/community/best-australian-blogs-comp/finalists-2014/</ref>

