'''Leon Jakimič''' (born February 23, 1975) is a Czech [[entrepreneur]], founder and owner of [[glassmaking]] company [[Lasvit]].
==Life and career== Leon Jakimič was born in [[Liberec]], [[Bohemia]] in 1975.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20150923175043/http://archive2012.belgradedesignweek.com/speaker/leon-jakimi%C4%87---lasvit]</ref> He received a [[tennis]] [[scholarship]] in [[California]] at [[Loyola Marymount University]] in [[Los Angeles]], where he studied [[Economics]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20140901095203/http://www.iluxurylife.cz/en/interview-leon-jakimic-master-light ]</ref> He graduated from the [[Kellogg-HKUST Executive MBA Program]] in 2005. In 2007 he founded [[Lasvit]], company designing and manufacturing bespoke [[light fitting]]s, feature glass installations, and lighting collections.<ref>[https://archive.is/20140507190345/http://www.worldofdesigners.com/glass-art-and-lighting-installations-by-lasvit/]</ref> Recently he lives in [[Hong Kong]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.domusweb.it/en/design/2012/02/20/lasvit-ancient-experience-young-passion.html |title=Lasvit: ancient experience, young passion - Design - Domus |website=Domusweb.it |date=2012-02-20 |accessdate=2017-02-23}}</ref>
