'''Lorenz Bogaert''', born 1976, is a [[Belgian]] online media entrepreneur. He is co-founder and CEO of [[Massive Media]],<ref name="Conard2009">{{cite book|last=Conard|first=Geert|title=Friends with Benefits, Networking in a New Economy|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7zjTaUER2BcC&pg=PA96|accessdate=29 May 2011|date=November 2009|publisher=Ecademy Press|isbn=978-1-905823-64-2|pages=96–}}</ref> a social media company owning digital brands such as [[social networking service]] [[Netlog]] and social dating community [[Twoo.com|Twoo]].  Bogaert studied law and management at the universities of Brussels (BE), Fribourg (CH) and Namur (BE). Lorenz lives in [[Ghent]].

