{{Infobox person | name = Walter H. Stuerzinger | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = 6 July 1955 | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Chief Operating Officer]], Corporate Center of [[UBS AG]] | spouse =}} '' Walter H. Stuerzinger'' (born 6 July 1955).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ubs.com/1/e/investors/corporategovernance/boardofdirectors/Stuerzinger.html?isPopup=yes |title=UBS profile |publisher=UBS |accessdate=2009-01-29}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] businessman. Mr Stuerzinger is Chief Operating Officer, Corporate Center at [[UBS AG]].
==Biography== Steurzinger holds a Swiss banking diploma and is a member of the Institute of Chartered Accountants. He worked with [[Credit Suisse]] on various assignments in the controlling and auditing areas. Before the [[UBS AG]] merger, he was Head Group Internal Audit at the former [[Union Bank of Switzerland]] and was Head Group Internal Audit from 1998 until 2001, and then Group Chief Risk Officer from 2001 until 2007. He joined the Group Executive Board at [[UBS AG]] in 2005. He was appointed Chief Operating Officer, Corporate Center in October 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/Walter-Stuerzinger-99570 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913223649/http://www.portfolio.com/resources/executive-profiles/Walter-Stuerzinger-99570 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2016-09-13 |title=Portfolio profile |publisher=Conde Nast |accessdate=2009-01-29}}</ref>
==Activities== Walter H. Stuerzinger is a member of the Foundation Board of the UBS Pension Fund. <ref>{{cite web|url= https://people.forbes.com/profile/walter-stuerzinger/81870 |title= Forbes profile |publisher= Forbes|accessdate=2009-01-29}}</ref> For further information, see as well here: [http://www.20min.ch/finance/dossier/ubskrise/story/28082536 News Paper article]
